Creating the User Model
-----------------------

1. Create new file: models/users.js

	- require mongoose
	- create the schema
	- name the model 'User'and attach it to the schema

2. Add code to store user details in the database (for checking is model is saving data to DB) in models/users.js

User.create({username: 'sam', password: 'sam'});
User.create({username: 'tom', password: 'tom'});

3. In app.js

	- require('./models/users');

4. Open mongo shell

	- mongo articlesDB
	- db.users.find()
	- confirm users are there
	- remove users:
		- db.users.remove({})


In this topic we learned how to create the user model to store user details in the database


